attributes.description: India Grid Trust (IndiGrid) is the India's first listed power sector infrastructure investment trust, sponsored by KKR and Sterlite Power. It was established in 2016 to own and operate power transmission and renewable energy assets in India.[1] The Trust primarily acquires operational transmission SPVs (Special Purpose Vehicles) from a Sponsor or from a third party. [2] The entity is not a public/ private company. It is an infrastructure investment trust (InvIT). There are no shareholders of a trust. Rather, there are unit holders who have the right to receive at-least 90% of the Net Distributable Cashflows of the Trust at least once in every six months in each financial year in accordance with the InvIT regulations. Also, a unitholder has no equitable or proprietary interest in the projects of IndiGrid and is not entitled to any share in the transfer of projects or any interest in the projects of IndiGrid.[3]
